WEBVTT

00:01.434 --> 00:04.503
        Cheers <i>is filmed</i>        
 <i>before a live studio audience.</i> 

00:04.571 --> 00:07.539
    Move it, you deadbeats.     
      We're closing early.      

00:07.640 --> 00:08.674
    Woody, our bartender's,     
        getting married,        

00:08.742 --> 00:09.775
      and we're all going       
        in the wedding.         

00:09.876 --> 00:11.377
Go on. Get the hell out of here.

00:11.444 --> 00:14.813
    If you're still thirsty,    
      go on over to Bob's.      

00:16.282 --> 00:19.952
     Gee, it's nice to see      
    my cousins again.           

00:21.254 --> 00:22.955
          You know, sitting here
            in my dinner jacket,

00:23.023 --> 00:24.890
              I feel I should be
                     tossing off

00:24.958 --> 00:28.494
             brittle Noel Coward
                    bon mots.   

00:29.696 --> 00:32.664
Do you know any brittle         
Noel Coward bon mots?           

00:32.732 --> 00:34.333
                     As a matter
                  of fact, I do.

00:34.401 --> 00:36.235
    It seems that after being   
         told that a very boring

00:36.302 --> 00:39.138
     acquaintance of his had put
     a bullet through his brain,

00:39.205 --> 00:43.876
      Coward said, "He must have
        been a remarkable shot!"

00:43.943 --> 00:47.446
Did he often find humor         
in the tragedy of others?       

00:47.514 --> 00:49.648
        Well, darling, you're   
        missing the humor, dear.

00:49.716 --> 00:51.817
He got his jollies              
from massive head trauma?       

00:51.885 --> 00:53.352
                        Don't...

00:53.420 --> 00:54.420
                  You're missing
                the whimsy...   

00:54.487 --> 00:56.021
Oh, for God's sake,             
Frasier!                        

00:56.089 --> 00:58.390
Can you imagine the state       
of mind that would drive a man  

00:58.458 --> 00:59.992
to do something like that?      

01:00.060 --> 01:02.394
Can you picture the despair     
he must have felt               

01:02.462 --> 01:06.498
facing a future in which        
any hope or joy seemed          
utterly impossible?             

01:06.566 --> 01:09.401
                I think I can   
             picture that, dear.

01:10.904 --> 01:13.939
      (theme song begins)       

